Rating: 3
Made this for dessert for my parents who aren't big sweet eaters. In the trail run, I peeled the pears. They held up much better with the skins. Roasting time varies based on the ripeness of the pears. If you have very ripe pears, they'll be mush after 20 minutes. All in all, a classic combination of flavors and a keeper for an easy, yet tasty, dessert.

Rating: 4
Desert for 25...this recipe is simple and fabulous. Make sure you get soft pears, mine were a little tough, and took longer to bake, but the end result was well worth it. I bought the port, but forgot to use it. but served with vanilla ice cream and 2 different drizzles for presentation - chocolate Raspberry & coffee caramel. Will definitely keep this in the recipe box!

Rating: 4
