Rating: 3
One of my favorite simple desserts. The brown sugar carmelized with the rosemary is wonderful and the gorgonzola is nicely balanced by the sweetness of the port. If you are not a fan of any of the ingredients, however, I would not recommend this one.

Rating: 3
This was so simple to prepare and had very lovely flavors. I served it with leftover turkey with port gravy (also from this website) and they matched beautifully. I noted a slight bitter aftertaste, and it may have been because the fresh rosemary was cooked too long. Fresh rosemary has a tendancy to get bitter when cooked too long. Next time, I will sprinkle it on halfway through baking. Make sure to use good port since it is poured on at the end and not cooked. If all your ingredients are good and fresh, this should work out well.

